# Make a Music Player
### @explicitHints true


## {Introduction @showdialog}

Before technology hits the market, it goes through many changes.

Today, you'll see what it might have been like to be on the prototype team for Zune back in 2005.

---

~hint What is a prototype? üí°

---

A prototype is an early model of something that has not yet been mass produced.

Prototypes don't always look or work the way the final product does, but they do allow inventors to see how their ideas will work in the real world.

hint~

---

![Zune outline](/static/tutorials/music/zune_outline.png "This is what the original Zune looked like back in 2006" )

---

In video games, a splash screen is a message that shows while a program or level is loading.

## {Step 9}

**‚ö° Here comes the action ‚ö°**

The game needs code to make the score go up
when the (A) button is clicked.


- :game: From the ``||controller:Controller||`` category, grab the
```block

    info.changeScoreBy(1)
})
```

## {Step 11}

This game is off to a great start...but it goes on forever! Add a countdown timer to give
the game an ending.

- :id card: Open the ``||info:Info||`` category and
drag the
```block
info.startCountdown(10)
```
block into **the bottom** of the<br/>
``||loops(noclick):on start||`` container.


~hint Click here to see how üïµüèΩ

![Add a countdown timer](/static/skillmap/star/countdown.gif "Put a timer at the end of your on start code")

hint~



#### ~ tutorialhint

```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`stage`)
let talent = sprites.create(assets.image`towering turtles`, SpriteKind.Player)
talent.bottom = 115
game.splash("Press (A) to play!")
//@highlight
info.startCountdown(10)
```
